Come and learn about a career path waiting for you in advanced manufacturing!
ApprenticeNYC for CNC Machinists is a paid, full-time apprenticeship opportunity that teaches NYC jobseekers the skills advanced manufacturing employers are looking for. Earn while you learn to become a Computer Numerically Controlled (CNC) Machinist. During this 18-month apprenticeship, you will learn how to work with CNC machinery from setup to operation to produce parts and tools from metal, plastic, and other materials.
Get Paid While You Learn - Starting pay as an apprentice is $16/hour and as you gain more skills, you may receive merit-based pay increases.
 Are You Eligible?

No experience necessary
18 years of age or older
A New York City resident
Have a High School Diploma or Equivalency
If this sounds like a good opportunity for you, register for ONE of the Information Sessions being offered in Queens, Brooklyn, Bronx & Staten Island every Tuesday & Thursday at either 9am or 2pm from Sept 24-October 24.
Please fill out the application before the information session – Click here.

Interested in a paid apprenticeship and a career as a Line Cook in a restaurant kitchen? Attend a First Course NYC Info Session.
First Course NYC is a new, 14-week culinary training program that will provide qualified New Yorkers access to entry-level Line Cook jobs and clear pathways to advancement and higher wages in respected NYC restaurants. 
In the first eight weeks of classroom kitchen training, participants will learn the fundamental culinary and job skills required to be an entry-level professional line cook. The training will be delivered at the Food Arts Center, a state-of-the-art kitchen training facility in midtown Manhattan. Participants will be paid a weekly stipend of $125/week during the initial eight-week training, and will receive weekly metrocards and daily meals.
The remaining six weeks of the program will offer an on-the-job apprenticeship in respected NYC restaurant kitchens at a rate of $16/hr. 
It is intended that qualified apprentices who successfully complete their training will continue with their employer as a full time entry-level line cook. 
Eligible Candidates must:

Be at least 18 years of age
Be a New York City resident
Be authorized to work in the United States
Be able to lift up to 40 pounds
Be able and willing to work flexible hours, including evenings, weekends, and holidays
Demonstrate a strong interest in, and enthusiasm for, food and for work in a restaurant kitchen

QuickBooks 
Learn the key features and benefits of this accounting software!Business owners need to monitor their spending and expenses in order to maintain a healthy profit. QuickBooks can help you keep track of daily transactions, as well as develop financial reports such as Income Statements, Balance Sheets, and Cash Flow Statements. This course will teach you how this software program can help you track your business financials effectively and efficiently. 
You will learn about:


Setting up your chart of accounts


Recording purchases, bills and accounts payable


Recording your sales, receive payments and make deposits


Creating reports that help you understand business performance


Please note, this course is designed to teach businesses how to use the software application. In order to benefit from this course, you must have a basic knowledge of business financials and computer applications.  If you are not familiar with concepts such as: categorizing revenues and expenses on an income statement, using a balance sheet, creating and using a cash flow statement, and accounting and bookkeeping methodology, you should register for Small Business Financing or Show Me The Money: Financial Statements & Profit as a pre-requisite
The Queens BSC will accept EventBrite course reservations and hold a seat for all registrants, however that does not guarantee admittance into the class. Upon submission of your registration, a staff member will reach out to you and provide an application for this class. Once an application is submitted the Queens BSC, we will conduct a phone interview at which point you will be advised of your acceptance into the class and confirm securing your seat.
Neighborhood 360° Fellows help community-based development organizations complete commercial revitalization projects and connect local stakeholders to City resources. Fellows are paid by SBS and are full-time community development professionals. Through the program, SBS aims to build a network of leaders prepared with commercial revitalization expertise and experience in New York City neighborhoods.  SBS is now accepting applications for 2020-2021 host site organizations. We are looking for Host Sites that meet these minimum criteria:


Nonprofit community-based development organization (Business Improvement Districts, local development corporations, merchants associations, and other organizations) operating in New York City and incorporated in New York State


Able to assist in recruiting candidates and interviewing finalist fellow applicants


Able to provide the fellow with a desk and supporting equipment (i.e. computer and access to organization's phone)


During the webinar, participating community-based organizations will gain:

An overview of the Neighborhood 360° Fellows program and expectations of host site organizations
Examples of projects conducted by previous cohorts
A detailed walk-through of the application process and selection timeline

Who should attend:

Senior staff and board members of NYC Business Improvement Districts, Chambers of Commerce, Merchants Associations, and other community-based organizations

Information on how to access the webinar will be sent out to those who RSVP.
Learn more about the Neighborhood 360° Fellows program here.

frequent_values:
The NYC Department of Small Business Services helps unlock economic potential and create economic security for all New Yorkers by connecting New Yorkers to good jobs, creating stronger businesses, and building thriving neighborhoods across the five boroughs.
You can register for all of our free events, courses, and WE NYC mentor sessions on Eventbrite. For questions about individual courses or to register over the phone, please contact our staff at one of our NYC Business Solutions Centers.
For more information on all of our services, call 311 or visit nyc.gov/sbs.
